Genetic interactions were considered significant if they had an SGA score of epsilon > 0.08 for positive interactions and epsilon < -0.08 for negative interactions, and a p-value < 0.05.

Author: Finnigan GC (2010)
Qualifications: A synthetic genetic array (SGA) screen was used to identify genes that caused an increase in calcium or zinc sensitivity in a vma21QQ voa1::Nat-R double mutant.  VOA1 is genetically linked to the VMA21 locus.  The vma21QQ mutant has a dysfunctional ER retrieval motif and complete deletion of VOA1 (voa1::Nat-R) results in a decrease in steady-state levels of Vma21p.
